{"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService"],"title":"Related Documentation","anchor":"Related-Documentation"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest"],"title":"How-to Guides","generated":true,"anchor":"How-to-Guides"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sell a lifetime entitlement alongside a subscription and surface both flags through the paywall plugin."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Many apps offer two ways to buy: a recurring pro subscription and a one-time lifetime purchase. RevenueCat models both as entitlements; ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" checks each independently and surfaces them as the two flags on ","type":"text"},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isPro"},{"text":" — active subscription.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasPermanentLicense"},{"text":" — active lifetime entitlement.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The paywall plugin’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"isGateSatisfied","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"isPro || hasPermanentLicense","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", so feature code keeps a single check while UI can branch on the underlying flags when it needs to.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For the entitlement-mapping rules and edge cases, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Before-you-start","text":"Before you start"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This guide assumes:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You have completed ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You have configured ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"two","type":"text"}]},{"text":" entitlements in the RevenueCat dashboard — typically ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pro"},{"text":" for the subscription and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lifetime"},{"text":" for the one-time purchase. The identifiers are arbitrary; only the strings need to match what you pass into the service.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-1-Pass-the-second-identifier","text":"Step 1: Pass the second identifier"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Replace the single-entitlement init with the two-arg form:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","","let service = RevenueCatPaywallService(","    entitlementID: \"pro\",","    permanentLicenseEntitlementID: \"lifetime\"",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Both entitlements are now checked on every ","type":"text"},{"code":"customerInfo()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"customerInfoStream()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" yield, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"restorePurchases()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call. The active state of ","type":"text"},{"code":"pro","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flows into ","type":"text"},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot.isPro","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; the active state of ","type":"text"},{"code":"lifetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flows into ","type":"text"},{"code":"hasPermanentLicense","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The two flags are independent. A user with both active gets both flags set; a user with only one active gets only that flag set.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-2-Wire-the-service-into-the-plugin","text":"Step 2: Wire the service into the plugin"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Same as the single-entitlement case — the plugin doesn’t need to know about the second identifier:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["plugins.register(","    PaywallPlugin<AppState, AppAction>(","        state: \\.paywall,","        action: AppAction.paywall,","        extractAction: { if case .paywall(let a) = $0 { return a }; return nil },","        service: RevenueCatPaywallService(","            entitlementID: \"pro\",","            permanentLicenseEntitlementID: \"lifetime\"","        )","    )",")"]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-3-Decide-whether-feature-code-needs-to-branch","text":"Step 3: Decide whether feature code needs to branch"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For most gated features, keep using ","type":"text"},{"code":"store.paywall.isGateSatisfied","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["if store.paywall.isGateSatisfied { … }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This stays correct whether the user has a subscription or a lifetime license, and works identically in apps that don’t sell a lifetime SKU.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-4-Branch-in-UI-when-copy-must-differ","text":"Step 4: Branch in UI when copy must differ"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the paywall sheet should be hidden for lifetime customers (so they’re not pestered to subscribe), or if the customer-center entry should be relabeled, branch on the underlying flag:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["if store.paywall.hasPermanentLicense {","    Text(\"Lifetime member — thank you!\")","} else if store.paywall.isPro {","    Button(\"Manage Subscription\") {","        store.send(.paywall(.presentCustomerCenter))","    }","} else {","    Button(\"Upgrade\") {","        store.send(.paywall(.request(reason: \"upgrade-prompt\")))","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Lifetime users typically have nothing to manage in App Store \/ Settings. Hiding the customer-center button for them avoids dead-end taps.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"When-to-skip-the-second-identifier","text":"When to skip the second identifier"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (or omit the parameter) if your app has no lifetime SKU:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["RevenueCatPaywallService(entitlementID: \"pro\")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"hasPermanentLicense","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" then stays ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" regardless of any entitlements RevenueCat reports — even if the dashboard accidentally has a ","type":"text"},{"code":"lifetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" entitlement that the service is not configured to check. See the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Lifetime entitlement is ignored when no permanent-license ID is configured","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" test case for the precise behavior.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}],"title":"How to Add a Permanent License","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoaddapermanentlicense"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToImplementService":{"abstract":[{"text":"Wire ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" plugin so the store sees real-time entitlement updates from RevenueCat.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoimplementservice","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","title":"How to Implement the Service"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/ServiceReference":{"title":"Service Reference","role":"article","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/servicereference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"API reference for ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — the RevenueCat-backed ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" conformer that the paywall plugin consumes.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SwiduxReve